    <div class="about-card mission">
      <h3>Our Mission</h3>
      <p>Heatscrapers empowers communities, planners and researchers with easy-to-understand visualizations of urban
        heat. We combine satellite data, open-source tools and user-friendly design to reveal where cities heat up and
        why.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="about-card what">
      <h3>What We Do</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Interactive heatmaps showing surface temperature patterns.</li>
        <li>Yearly heat timelines to track long-term trends.</li>
        <li>Comparative tools to study neighborhoods and cities.</li>
        <li>Open data and reproducible code for researchers.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>


    <div class="about-card how">
      <h3>How It Works</h3>
      <p>We fetch and process satellite-derived temperature data, combine it with local weather and mapping APIs, then
        visualize the results using Leaflet and Cal‑Heatmap. Our backend aggregates daily values into calendar timelines
        and geospatial heatpoints.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="about-card impact">
      <h3>Impact</h3>
      <p>By making heat data accessible, Heatscrapers helps identify urban hot-spots, informs cooling strategies, and
        supports climate resilience planning at the local scale.</p>
    </div>
  </div>


